items.name: Coal

items.name: Mistletoe
items.description: Have you been nice?

items.name: Indestructable Climbing Pick
items.description: Climb up and hang from nearly any surface with these!

items.name: Reusable Bola
items.description: Wind it up and throw! Infinite use.

items.name: Reusable Flare Gun
items.description: A infinite-use flare launcher. Fires a bright ball of Sparkpowder to temporarily light an area.

items.name: Reusable Grappling Hook
items.description: Apply on the Crossbow to grapple onto the environment & other creatures. Primary Fire to "Reel-In", Secondary Fire to "Reel-Out", Crouch to Detach, Jump + Reel-In to Vault-Jump!

items.name: Reusable Grappling Hook
items.description: Primary Fire to "Reel-In", Secondary Fire to "Reel-Out", Crouch to Detach, Jump + Reel-In to Vault-Jump!

items.name: Reusable Parachute
items.description: Use this while falling to slow your fall. Jump while parachuting to deactivate it. Infinite use.

items.name: Reusable Spear
items.description: A easily made melee weapon that can also be thrown.  Does not break when used. Infinite use.

items.name: Mindwipe Tonic 12hr Cooldown
items.description: Drink this tonic to forget everything you have learned (resets your Engram Points). Usable once every 12 hours.

items.name: Super Spyglass
items.description:
- Detailed stats
- Shows (Wild - Tamed) level up points
- Variable zoom
- Increased range

items.name: Aquatic Mushroom
items.description: A wavy blueish-green mushroom with a glowing edge. Looks refreshing.

items.name: Ascerbic Mushroom
items.description: A mushroom as black as a moonless midnight. Looks to be highly narcotic.

items.name: Auric Mushroom
items.description: An oily-looking mushroom which glitters gold even in the dimmest light. Looks invigorating!

items.name: Nameless Venom
items.description: A volatile substance that can be used to raise Rock Drakes!

items.name: Plant Species Z Fruit
items.description: Bioluminescent Fruit that provides a flash of Charge lighting

items.name: Amarberry
items.description: This yellow berry grows mostly on the beaches.  Tasty, and can be used to make yellow dye.

items.name: Azulberry
items.description: This blue berry grows mostly in dense jungles.  Tasty, and can be used to make blue dye.

items.name: Mejoberry
items.description: This wild berry grows mostly on mountains.  While not tasty on its own, its juices improve almost every meal.

items.name: Narcoberry
items.description: This fairly common black berry makes you sleepy when you eat it.  Bitter, but can be used to make black dye.

items.name: Stimberry
items.description: This fairly common white berry can be eaten in a pinch to recover Food, Stamina, and lose Torpidity, but it will dehydrate you.  Bitter, but can be used to make white dye.

items.name: Tintoberry
items.description: This red berry grows mostly in wide open grasslands.  Tasty, and can be used to make red dye.

items.name: Blood Pack
items.description: Use this to replace lost blood.  Restores Health over time.

items.name: Bug Repellant
items.description: This gnarly paste makes you nearly invisible to bugs, bats, and spiders. Just don't attack them or get too close, and they'll ignore you! Effect lasts 10 minutes.

items.name: Cactus Broth
items.description: This magical soup will greatly reduce your water consumption. The aroma of the cactus has a side effect of making the wildlife notice you less.

items.name: Cactus Sap
items.description: Cut of cactus that giving sap and when it is consumed hydrates your body

items.name: Cooked Lamb Chop
items.description:
Sates your hunger, and provides health while being digested.  More effective than prime meat. 
Wild carnivores LOVE this meat!

items.name: Cooked Meat
items.description: Sates your hunger, and provides health while being digested.  Wild carnivores will eat it, but prefer raw meat.

items.name: Cooked Fish Meat
items.description: Sates your hunger SLIGHTLY, and provides health while being digested.  Wild carnivores will eat it, but prefer raw meat.

items.name: Cooked Meat Jerky
items.description:
Sates your hunger, and provides health while being digested.  Lasts longer than cooked meat.
Wild carnivores will eat it, but prefer raw meat.

items.name: Cooked Prime Meat
items.description:
Sates your hunger, and provides health while being digested.  More effective than normal meat.
Wild carnivores like this meat a lot.

items.name: Cooked Prime Fish Meat
items.description: Sates your hunger SLIGHTLY, and provides health while being digested.  More effective than normal meat. Wild carnivores like this meat a lot.

items.name: Prime Meat Jerky
items.description:
Sates your hunger, and provides health while being digested.  More effective than normal meat jerky, and lasts longer than cooked prime meat.
Wild carnivores like this meat a lot.

items.name: Lesser Antidote
items.description: Cures Lesser Afflictions!

items.name: Medical Brew
items.description: This brew doesn't have any nutritional value, but it promotes healing.

items.name: Giant Bee Honey
items.description: A delicious and nutritious snack, useful for luring creatures to a trap or for fishing.

items.name: Bio Toxin
items.description: Powerful toxin harvested from an organism.

items.name: Narcotic
items.description: Increases your health, but puts you to sleep.

items.name: Raw Meat
items.description: Eating raw food will sate hunger, but is unhealthy for humans.  Most wild carnivores prefer raw meat to cooked meat.

items.name: Raw Fish Meat
items.description: Eating raw food will SLIGHTLY sate hunger, but is unhealthy for humans.  Most wild carnivores prefer raw meat to cooked meat.

items.name: Raw Mutton
items.description:
Eating raw food will sate hunger, but is unhealthy for humans.  This excellent cut spoils very quickly.
Most wild carnivores love this meat.

items.name: Raw Prime Meat
items.description:
Eating raw food will sate hunger, but is unhealthy for humans.  This excellent cut spoils very quickly.
Most wild carnivores love this meat.

items.name: Raw Prime Fish Meat
items.description: Eating raw food will SLIGHTLY sate hunger, but is unhealthy for humans.  This excellent cut spoils very quickly. Most wild carnivores love this meat.

items.name: Battle Tartare
items.description: This dish grants you almost combat prowess of a berserker.  Consume it to gain massively increased melee damage, move speed, damage resistance, and stamina regen.  Also causes you to consume food and water more quickly, and lose health.  Effects last 3 minutes.

items.name: Calien Soup
items.description: This simple vegetarian dish refreshes your body like an oasis.  Consume it to gain increased hyperthermic insulation, and slow your rate of water consumption.  Effects last 15 minutes.

items.name: Enduro Stew
items.description: This hearty dish is like a workout in the form of a meal.  Consume it to deal increased melee damage, and gain extra stamina regen.  Effects last 15 minutes.

items.name: Focal Chili
items.description: This filling dish is full of nutritional energy.  Consume it to gain increased craft speed, and gain increased movement speed.  Effects last 15 minutes.

items.name: Fria Curry
items.description: This spicy vegetarian dish fills the body with a comfortable warmth.  Consume it to gain increased hypothermic insulation, and slow your rate of food consumption.  Effects last 15 minutes.

items.name: Lazarus Chowder
items.description: This creamy dish improves the body's natural constitution.  Consume it to slow your rate of oxygen consumption while underwater, and gain extra health regen.  Effects last 15 minutes.

items.name: Shadow Steak Saute
items.description: This dish grants you a hunters instinct.  Consume it to ignore most weather, and steady your aim. Effects last 3 minutes.

items.name: Spoiled Meat
items.description:
Eww... do not eat.
This must have a use, right?

items.name: Energy Brew
items.description: This brew doesn't have any nutritional value, but fills your stamina.

items.name: Stimulant
items.description: Keeps you awake, but dehydrates you.

items.name: Sweet Vegetable Cake
items.description: A sappy vegetable cake which Herbivores find delicious, which will be automatically eaten when needed for healing. Alas, humans and carnivores tend to find its taste repugnant.

items.name: Broth of Enlightenment
items.description: A single sip of this incredible broth will expand your mind and broaden your horizons, granting greatly increased experience gain for a brief time.

items.name: Citronal
items.description: This citrus fruit grows naturally along the coast.  It will probably prevent scurvy.

items.name: Longrass
items.description: This grain plant grows best in open, fertile areas.  It can be eaten by the cob, but more clever chefs will think of other options.

items.name: Rockarrot
items.description: This root vegetable seems to thrive near mammals, and not dinosaurs.  As such, it can be found mostly in the mountains.

items.name: Savoroot
items.description: This starchy tuber grows naturally in densely wooded areas.  It is very hearty, but tastes better when cooked.

items.name: Element Ore
items.description: Unrefined Element.

items.name: Fungal Wood
items.description: A thick, sturdy cutting from a huge mushroom. Has all of the properties of a chunk of wood!

items.name: Green Gem
items.description: This strange Gem is used as a crafting ingredient in primitive tools and saddles.

items.description: This strange sap has unique properties that make it an ideal replacement for Blue Gems

items.name: Condensed Gas
items.description: A highly concentrated and hardened gas deposit. This could be refined back into it's gaseous form.

items.name: Corrupted Nodule
items.description: These incredibly strong, lightweight nodules are somehow naturally made in corrupted creatures. Incredibly hazardous to human health if consumed.

items.name: Fungal Wood
items.description: A thick, sturdy cutting from a corrupted tree. Has all of the properties of a chunk of wood!

items.description: Refined Element Dust that is unstable. Over time it will stabilize and become element.

items.description: A strange, highly advanced material humming with energy. It dissolves when transferred across ARKs.

items.description: Used in very specialized Recipes...
